msgid "The Elevation Profile Item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/print_layout/layout_items/layout_elevation_profile.rst:13
msgid ""
"The Elevation Profile item is used to display an :ref:`elevation profile "
"view <label_elevation_profile_view>` in a layout. Use the "
"|elevationProfile| :guilabel:`Add Elevation Profile` button, and follow "
":ref:`items creation instructions <create_layout_item>` to add a new "
"elevation profile item that you can later manipulate the same way as "
"demonstrated in :ref:`interact_layout_item`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/print_layout/layout_items/layout_elevation_profile.rst:136
msgid "elevationProfile"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/print_layout/layout_items/layout_elevation_profile.rst:18
msgid ""
"A new elevation profile item has default settings that make it render an "
"empty chart. You can customize its properties in the :guilabel:`Item "
"Properties` panel. In addition to the :ref:`common properties "
"<item_common_properties>`, this feature has the following "
"functionalities:"
msgstr ""

