#: ../../docs/user_manual/print_layout/layout_items/layout_elevation_profile.rst:61
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Tolerance` distance, which can be data-defined, helps you "
"control how far a feature of the visible layers should be from the "
"profile curve in order to display in the layout elevation view. Only "
"point features are currently returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/print_layout/layout_items/layout_elevation_profile.rst:65
msgid ""
"Under the :guilabel:`Show Subsections Indicator` group, It is possible to"
" highlight the position of the vertices of the curve on the Elevation "
"Profile. Activate |checkbox| :guilabel:`Show Subsections Indicator` to "
"display vertical lines at the distances of the vertices. Use the "
":guilabel:`Lines` drop-down list to set the symbol, color, opacity and "
"width of the Subsections Indicator lines."
msgstr ""

